    <h2 class="entry-title">
        NIAID Antimicrobial Resistance Sequencing Projects
    </h2>
    <section class="main">
        <div class="data-box">
            <h3 class="ribbon-title">NIAID Antimicrobial Resistance Sequencing Projects</h3>
            <p><a href="http://gsc.jcvi.org/"
                  target="_blank"><img src="http://enews.patricbrc.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/J-craig-venter.jpeg"
                                       alt="J-craig-venter" width="180" height="50"></a>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<a
                    href="http://www.broadinstitute.org/science/projects/gscid/genomic-sequencing-center-infectious-diseases"
                    target="_blank"><img
                    src="http://enews.patricbrc.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Broad-logo-300x75.jpeg" alt="Broad logo"
                    width="208" height="53"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<a
                    href="http://gscid.igs.umaryland.edu/"

                    target="_blank"><img src="http://enews.patricbrc.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/UMSM.jpeg"
                                         alt="UMSM" width="223" height="59"></a></p>
            <p>The following sequencing projects completed by the GCIDs have a focus on understanding antimicrobial
                resistance (AMR). The metadata provided by the GCID collaborators has been included at PATRIC to
                facilitate research on AMR and initial analysis capabilities are available. &nbsp;Where AMR “panel data”
                was provided by the collaborators, a spreadsheet is available to <a
                        href="ftp://ftp.patricbrc.org/BRC_Mirrors/AMR/PATRIC_genomes_AMR.xlsx">download</a> from PATRIC
                containing the combined information. &nbsp; This is just an initial step at including genome-based AMR
                capabilities at PATRIC. &nbsp; Additional genome sets and analysis capabilities will be added in the
                coming months.</p>
            <p>For more information about each projects, follow the project title link to the information available from
                the individual sequencing centers.</p>
